    "claim": "`cook()` marks `status.needsSolvencyCheck = true` after `_borrow()` and `_removeCollateral()`, but `ACTION_ACCRUE` is never handled and any unrecognized action falls through to `_additionalCookAction()`. In the base contract that hook has an empty implementation, so it returns a zeroed `CookStatus` and wipes the pending solvency check before the final `_isSolvent()` gate runs.",
    "impact": "A user can borrow MIM without sufficient collateral by ending the batch with `ACTION_ACCRUE` (or another unsupported action), or withdraw collateral from an already-borrowing position and skip the insolvency revert. This is a direct drain of cauldron liquidity and leaves the system with bad debt.",
    "paths": [
      "cook([ACTION_BORROW, ACTION_ACCRUE], ...) -> `_borrow()` transfers MIM and sets `needsSolvencyCheck` -> `ACTION_ACCRUE` falls into `_additionalCookAction()` -> returned zeroed status clears the flag -> final solvency check is skipped",
      "cook([ACTION_REMOVE_COLLATERAL, ACTION_ACCRUE], ...) -> `_removeCollateral()` transfers collateral and sets `needsSolvencyCheck` -> trailing unsupported action clears the flag -> borrower exits with debt still outstanding"
    ]
  },
