    "claim": "`init()` ignores the success flag returned by `oracle.get()` and stores whatever `rate` value comes back. If a clone is initialized while the oracle is failing or returns zero, `exchangeRate` can be set to 0/stale, and later solvency checks will keep reusing that cached value whenever `updateExchangeRate()` cannot refresh it.",
    "impact": "A freshly deployed clone can start life with an effectively broken solvency model. Attackers only need negligible collateral to pass `_isSolvent()` and can drain the clone’s available MIM until the oracle begins returning valid data again, leaving bad debt once a real rate is restored.",
